data.title: Dodge County High School
data.meta_description: Dodge County High School school profile, performance trends and GA state ranking. See how Dodge County High School ranks with other Eastman schools.
data.text:
Summary:

Dodge County High School is a public high school in Eastman, Georgia, serving 834 students in grades 9-12. The school is part of the Dodge County School District, which is ranked 117 out of 193 districts in the state and has a 2-star rating from SchoolDigger.

Dodge County High School has a diverse student population, with 56.59% White, 31.18% African American, and 7.43% Hispanic students. The school has maintained high four-year graduation rates, ranging from 94.4% to 98.5% over the past five years. However, its test scores on the Milestones Assessments are generally lower than the state averages, with proficiency rates ranging from 7.1% to 48.2% across different subjects and years. The school also has a high percentage of students receiving free or reduced-price lunch, ranging from 55.45% to 67.75% over the past three years.

Compared to nearby schools like West Laurens High School and Bleckley County High School, Dodge County High School's performance is generally lower, with lower test scores, graduation rates, and a declining statewide ranking. The nearby alternative schools, such as DAC (Dodge County Achievement Center) and Telfair Alternative Preparation School, also have significantly lower performance indicators, suggesting the challenges faced by these specialized schools.
